results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of graphs on n unlabeled nodes with total domination number k, n >= 2, 2 <= k <= n.
comment: Only graphs without isolated nodes can have a total dominating set.
The total domination number of a graph is greater than or equal to the domination number.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Total Domination Number
